1. Install Windows 10

this requires a valid Windows 10 license and the necessary installation media. i follow the  on-screen instructions during the Windows 10 installation process.

2. Install Visual Studio

   Download the Visual Studio installer from the official Microsoft website.
Run the installer and choose the "Desktop development with C++" workload (or the workload specific to your development needs).
During installation, I customize components by selecting specific languages and tools I'll be using.

3. Install Git for Version Control with GitHub

Downloading  the Git Bash installer from the official Git website.
Run the installer and choose the default installation options. This will add Git and command-line tools to your system.
Create a free GitHub account (https://github.com/join) to use Git for version control and collaboration.
4. Install Python Programming Language

Download the latest Python installer from the official Python website.
Run the installer and ensure "Add Python 3.x to PATH" is checked. This allows you to run Python commands from the command prompt.
Verify the installation by opening a command prompt and typing python --version. This should display the installed Python version.
5. Install MySQL Database

Download the MySQL Community Server installer from the official MySQL website.
Run the installer and choose the "Developer Default" configuration.
During installation, set a strong root password for the MySQL server. You'll need this password to connect to the database from your applications.
Once installed, you can access the MySQL command line tool by running mysql in your command prompt.
Configurations and Customizations:

Visual Studio: Explore the extensive customization options within Visual Studio to personalize your development experience. You can install extensions, customize themes, and configure keyboard shortcuts for improved efficiency.
Git: Familiarize yourself with Git commands for version control. Resources like the official Git documentation (https://git-scm.com/doc) are helpful for learning the basics.
Python: Consider installing additional Python libraries and frameworks using pip, the Python package installer, to expand your development capabilities.
MySQL: Explore the MySQL Workbench (https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/workbench/) for a graphical user interface to manage your MySQL databases.
Troubleshooting:

Visual Studio Installation Issues: no issue encounterred
Git Setup Issues: no issue encountered

Python Installation Issues:difficulty in making choise of version to install.

MySQL Installation Issues: If encountering errors during MySQL installation, refer to the MySQL documentation for troubleshooting steps specific to your error messages.